<h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>

<p><strong>Personal Information You Provide</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>Name</li>
  <li>Email address</li>
  <li>Phone number (if provided)</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Health and Fitness Data</strong></p>
<p>
  The App allows you to track habits and fitness information such as workouts,
  daily goals, and progress entries. This data is stored on our secure servers
  to enable features like streak tracking, progress history, and syncing across devices.
</p>

<p><strong>Automatically Collected Information</strong></p>
<ul>
  <li>Device information (device type, operating system, unique device identifiers)</li>
  <li>Usage data (app interactions, session duration)</li>
  <li>Advertising identifiers (Google Advertising ID or Apple Identifier for Advertisers)</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Payment Information</strong></p>
<p>
  We do not collect or store payment card details. In-app purchases and
  subscriptions are processed securely by Google Play Billing (Android) or
  Apple In-App Purchase (iOS). Subscription management is also handled via
  RevenueCat. None of these services share your payment card details with us.
</p>

<p><strong>Advertising Data (Google AdMob)</strong></p>
<p>
  We use Google AdMob to display advertisements to non-subscribed users.
  AdMob may collect and use data such as your advertising ID, device information,
  and ad interaction data to provide personalised advertising.
</p>

<h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
<ul>
  <li>To create and manage your account</li>
  <li>To provide, maintain, and improve habit and fitness tracking features</li>
  <li>To process in-app purchases and subscriptions via the app stores</li>
  <li>To communicate with you (account notifications, support)</li>
  <li>To display relevant advertisements via Google AdMob (free users only)</li>
  <li>For internal analytics to understand app usage and improve user experience</li>
  <li>To comply with legal obligations</li>
</ul>
<p>We do not sell your personal information to third parties.</p>

<h2>3. Sharing of Your Information</h2>
<p>We may share your information in the following limited circumstances:</p>
<ul>
  <li>With Google (AdMob advertising) and the app stores (Google Play, Apple App Store) as necessary for their services</li>
  <li>With RevenueCat for subscription management</li>
  <li>With service providers who assist in operating the App (under confidentiality agreements)</li>
  <li>If required by law, regulation, or legal process</li>
  <li>In connection with a merger, acquisition, or sale of assets (with appropriate protections)</li>
</ul>
<p>
  We do not share your health/fitness data or personal contact information
  with advertisers or for marketing purposes beyond the App's functionality.
</p>

<h2>4. Data Security</h2>
<p>
  We implement reasonable administrative, technical, and physical safeguards to
  protect your personal information. However, no method of transmission over the
  internet or electronic storage is 100% secure. While we strive to protect your
  data, we cannot guarantee absolute security.
</p>

<h2>5. Data Retention</h2>
<p>
  We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfil the
  purposes outlined in this policy or as required by law. You may request
  deletion of your account and associated data by contacting us at the email above.
</p>

<h2>6. Your Rights and Choices</h2>
<p>Depending on your location, you may have rights to:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Access, correct, or delete your personal information</li>
  <li>Opt out of personalised advertising</li>
  <li>Withdraw consent where applicable</li>
</ul>
<p>
  To exercise these rights, contact us at
  <a href="mailto:bellgadevelopments@gmail.com">bellgadevelopments@gmail.com</a>.
</p>
<p>For advertising preferences:</p>
<ul>
  <li>Android: reset your Advertising ID or opt out in device Settings → Privacy</li>
  <li>iOS: limit ad tracking in Settings → Privacy &amp; Security → Tracking</li>
</ul>
<p>
  Learn more about Google's data practices:
  <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank">Google Privacy Policy</a>
</p>

<h2>7. Children's Privacy</h2>
<p>
  Our App is not intended for children under the age of 13 (or 16 in some
  jurisdictions). We do not knowingly collect personal information from children.
  If we become aware that we have collected such data, we will take steps to delete it.
</p>

<h2>8. International Transfers</h2>
<p>
  Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries outside
  Australia (including the United States). We take appropriate measures to ensure
  your data receives adequate protection in accordance with applicable law.
</p>

<h2>9. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
